2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on understanding the computations at each layer of deep neural networks, which is a key area of research in neural computing. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions the possible application of the findings in understanding how a sensory hierarchy works, which is a topic of interest in computer vision. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the interpretability of deep neural networks, which is a key area of research in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the mechanisms of dimensionality reduction and decorrelation in deep neural networks, which can be relevant to the design and control of complex systems.
